description:
D4DJ Double Mix is a self-contained special episode centering around the groups Merm4id and RONDO.

"D4 FES.", a DJ festival that has been described as legendary, was relaunched, and Merm4id's long-cherished wish to participate came true. Marika Mizushima, Saori Hidaka, and Dalia Matsuyama are concerned about the unusual behavior of Rika Seto during the swimsuit photo shoot. Meanwhile, RONDO's Tsubaki Aoyagi is alone in the chapel, indulging her hopes for the future how their world will be expanded.

One day, after a live concert at the clubhouse ALTER-EGO, Rika rushes into Tsubaki's place where she is with Nagisa Tsukimiyama, Hiiro Yano, and Aoi Miyake. She, who overcomes everything with luck and charm in order to enjoy life, makes a surprising proposal.

(Source: Crunchyroll, edited)
synonyms: Dig Delight Direct Drive DJ Double Mix

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/oichanmusi) | [Bluesky](https://bsky.app/profile/oichanmusi.bsky.social) | [Website](https://hifumi-inc.co.jp/team/mizushima-seiji/)

After graduating from Tokyo Designers' Gakuin College, Mizushima joined [Tokyo Animation Film](https://anilist.co/studio/899/). While doing photography work at the beginning of his career he studied under director of photography [Masahiro Kumagai](https://anilist.co/staff/174419/). He later went to work for [Sunrise](https://anilist.co/studio/14/) as a production assistant, aiming to become a full-fledged director.

Mizushima debuted as an episode director in 1993 on [Kouryuu Densetsu Villgust](https://anilist.co/anime/2049/), aiding the director of the OVA [Katsuhiko Nishijima](https://anilist.co/staff/103059/). In 1998, he made his proper directorial debut with [Generator Gawl](https://anilist.co/anime/1022/). He has since gone on to direct numerous shows, among which [Shaman King](https://anilist.co/anime/154/), [Fullmetal Alchemist](https://anilist.co/anime/121/) and [Oh! Edo Rocket](https://anilist.co/anime/2152/).

He often cites [Hideaki Anno](https://anilist.co/staff/100111/) as an anime director that he respects.

Affiliated with Studio Anima.

_Note: Not to be confused with the [background artist](https://anilist.co/staff/156392/)._

[Website](http://www.nakamurakou.com/) | [Blog](http://kou.livedoor.biz/) | [Twitter](https://twitter.com/nkkou)

Kou Nakamura is a novelist and winner of the 39th Bungei Prize in 2002. He also won the Noma Literary Newcomer Prize in 2004.

_Note: Not to be confused with the [animator](https://anilist.co/staff/159869/Ami-Satou)._

[Twitter](https://twitter.com/satoami_satoami)

RONDO is an all-girl DJ group in the Dig Delight Direct Drive DJ franchise. Their genre is an eclectic mix of heavy alternative metal music and electronic elements.

The group consists of four members:

- [Rihona Katou](https://anilist.co/staff/204571/Rihona-Katou) as [Tsubaki Aoyagi](https://anilist.co/character/204570/Tsubaki-Aoyagi)
- [Sae Otsuka](https://anilist.co/staff/120235/Sae-Otsuka) as [Nagisa Tsukimiyama](https://anilist.co/character/206279/Nagisa-Tsukimiyama)
- [Haruna Momono](https://anilist.co/staff/139262/Haruna-Momono) as [Hiiro Yano](https://anilist.co/character/206282/Hiiro-Yano)
- [Tsunko](https://anilist.co/staff/206301/Tsunko) as [Aoi Miyake](https://anilist.co/character/206288/Aoi-Miyake)

Merm4id is an all-girl DJ group in the Dig Delight Direct Drive DJ franchise. They are a DJ unit with a goal of becoming famous. Their music genre consists of EDM, Electro House, and Progressive Trance.

The group is comprised of 4 members:

- [Natsumi Hirajima](https://anilist.co/staff/204569/Natsumi-Hirajima) as [Rika Seto](https://anilist.co/character/204568/Rika-Seto)
- [Mei Okada](https://anilist.co/staff/206239/Mei-Okada) as [Marika Mizushima](https://anilist.co/character/206238/Marika-Mizushima)
- [Himari Hazuki](https://anilist.co/staff/204710/Himari-Hazuki) as [Saori Hidaka](https://anilist.co/character/206240/Saori-Hidaka)
- [Ai Negishi](https://anilist.co/staff/206242/Ai-Negishi) as [Dalia Matsuyama](https://anilist.co/character/206241/Dalia-Matsuyama)
